es of the warm\nabsorber could be detected. The spectrum shows absorption from Fe-UTA,\n\\ion{O}{iv}, and \\ion{O}{v}, consistent to belong to the lower-ionization\ncounterpart of the historical NGC 5548 warm absorber. Hence, we confirm that\nthe warm absorber has responded to the drop in the ionizing luminosity caused\nby the obscurer.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 May 2015 10:53:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-12"}
